    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving M96 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six. Mated to a precise 6-speed G96 manual transaxle, the powertrain delivers linear torque across the rev range thanks to VarioCam Plus variable valve timing. The chassis remains taut with upgraded Bilstein dampers and refreshed control arm bushings, preserving the communicative feedback of the original hydraulic steering rack. Recent preventative maintenance includes an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a new rear main seal, addressing critical failure points for long-term reliability. The braking system utilizes four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors for consistent thermal management and immediate bite. This is a well-sorted machine for the purist seeking visceral engagement and mechanical honesty.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
